# Specs stay current

When you change **behavior**, **architecture**, **user-visible UX**, **CLI/TUI contracts**, or **testing/CI expectations**, update the relevant files under **`specs/`** in the **same change** (same PR / same session).

- Prefer the smallest set of docs: e.g. `specs/tui-architecture.md` for TUI structure, `specs/tui-ux.md` for UX summaries, `specs/tui-screens.md` per screen, `specs/AGENTS.md` for phase/status when reality shifts.
- Do **not** leave specs describing old behavior after the code has moved on.
- If unsure which file to touch, start from `specs/tui-README.md` or `specs/README.md`.

Normative alongside `specs/AGENTS.md` § PR / merge discipline.

